comments: Replay review of the foul called on VanVleet (HOU) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful.  VanVleet clamps and holds Kessler's (UTA) arm, which affects his pursuit of the rebound.
Whitmore (HOU) establishes a wide screening position in Sexton's (UTA) path, and the contact occurs to his leg.
Whitmore (HOU) legally contests Clarkson's (UTA) jump shot attempt.
Kessler (UTA) is moving alongside Sengun's (HOU) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Sengun (HOU) is bracing for the contact from Kessler (UTA), and marginal contact occurs as he releases away from the contact.
Kessler (UTA) is raising his left arm into a vertical position to contest the shot, and marginal contact occurs with Sengun's (HOU) left arm as he removes his left hand from the ball.
Smith Jr. (HOU) and Markkanen (UTA) briefly engage and disengage as they pursue the rebound.
Clarkson (UTA) is bracing for the contact from Green (HOU), and marginal contact occurs as he releases away from the contact.
Brooks (HOU) moves forward towards Clarkson (HOU) and marginal contact occurs as Clarkson passes the ball.
Kessler (UTA) cleanly deflects the ball away from Sengun (HOU) as they pursue the rebound.
The Jazz signal for, and are awarded, a timeout prior to any contact between Smith Jr. (HOU) and Markkanen (UTA).
Brooks (HOU) initiates contact with Sexton's (UTA) wrist, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Dunn (UTA) lowers his hand and makes contact with Whitmore's (HOU) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Clarkson (UTA) moves forward into Smith Jr.'s (HOU) lower body and affects his ability to secure the rebound.
Kessler (UTA) retreats his arm into a vertical position and the contact with Sengun (HOU) is marginal.
Sexton (UTA) does not maintain legal guarding position and initiates contact with Sengun's (HOU) arm that affects his shot near the rim.
Thompson (HOU) legally contests Sexton's (UTA) jump shot attempt.
Sengun (HOU) grabs and holds Kessler's (UTA) arm as Kessler secures possession.
Green (HOU) and Sexton (UTA) come together at the same spot in pursuit of the rebound, and incidental foot to foot contact occurs.
Sengun (HOU) extends his leg out and kicks the ball on the play.
Brooks (HOU) briefly grasps Markkanen's (UTA) arm during the inbound, and the contact is marginal.
Kessler (UTA) and Thompson (HOU) each make clean contact with the ball as Kessler pulls it away from Thompson.
Sexton (UTA) makes contact with the part of Thompson's (HOU) hand that is on the ball, and Kessler (UTA) simultaneously makes clean contact with the ball as he defends Thompson's shot.
Brooks (HOU) is moving alongside Clarkson's (UTA) path and the contact on the perimeter is marginal.
Kessler (UTA) does not establish himself in Brooks' (HOU) path, and takes an extra step into Brooks' path and delivers contact during the pick.
Kessler (UTA) initiates contact with Sengun's (HOU) head during the layup attempt.
Brooks (HOU) brings his arm toward Sexton's (UTA) path and marginal contact occurs at the start of Sexton's drive.
Sexton (UTA) initiates contact with Smith Jr. (HOU) that affects his ability to secure the rebound.
Sexton (UTA) is bracing for the contact from Holiday (HOU) and marginal contact occurs as he releases away from the contact.
Thompson (HOU) cleanly blocks Sexton's (UTA) driving shot attempt.
Kessler (UTA) jumps forward into Sengun's (HOU) body and delivers contact prior to making any contact with the ball.
Tate (HOU) contests Clarkson's (UTA) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
